msgid "How to require 3rd Party Libs ?"
msgstr "如何需要第三方库？ ???"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "<span class=\"weex-version\">0.4</span>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the paragraph [Maintain Your Component Code](./maintain-your-component-code.md), we learn that JavaScript code can be written in `<script>` tag in one component. But there must be some common functions or modules in your project, such as parsing url params, extending properties from some objects to another object and so on. It's a bad practice to copy and paste them in each component, therefore there's a urgent need of `require`. Weex provides CommonJS `require` syntax for developers.\n"
msgstr "在段落[保持你的组件代码](./maintain-your-component-code.md)，我们学习JavaScript代码可以写在`<script>`` tag in one component. But there must be some common functions or modules in your project, such as parsing url params, extending properties from some objects to another object and so on. It's a bad practice to copy and paste them in each component, therefore there's a urgent need of ``require``. Weex provides CommonJS ``require`语法对于开发商。 ???\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:7
msgid "Let take `extend` for example."
msgstr "让我们采取`extend`例如。 ???"

#. type: Title ##
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Require Local Js Modules"
msgstr "要求本地js模块 ???"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:11
msgid ""
"A basic implementation of `extend` is as follows, and it's placed in "
"directory path `./common/utils.js`."
msgstr ""
"对`extend`` is as follows, and it's placed in directory path ``./common/"
"utils.js`基本实现。 ???"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"function extend(dest, src) {\n"
"  for (var key in src) {\n"
"    dest[key] = src[key]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"exports.extend = extend\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:22
msgid "In a `.we` file, `extend` can be used with the help of `require`:"
msgstr ""
"在`.we`` file, ``extend`` can be used with the help of ``require`： ???"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"<script>\n"
"  var utils = require('./common/utils')\n"
"  var obj1 = {a: 1}\n"
"  var obj2 = {b: 2}\n"
"  utils.extend(obj1, obj2) // obj1 => {a: 1, b: 2}\n"
"</script>\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Require Installed Node Modules"
msgstr "需要安装的节点模块 ???"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:35
msgid ""
"Besides, [underscore](http://underscorejs.org) is a JavaScript library that "
"provides a whole mess of useful functional programming helpers without "
"extending any built-in objects. It implements a more robust version of "
"[extend](http://underscorejs.org/#extend)."
msgstr ""
"此外，[强调](http://underscorejs.org)是一个JavaScript库，提供了一个有用的功能"
"编程助手乱不延长任何内置对象。它实现了一个更强大的版本的[延伸](http://"
"underscorejs.org/#extend)。 ???"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:37
msgid ""
"We can use underscore's extend instead of the version implemented by "
"ourselves. After installing `underscore` to the `node_modules` directory, we "
"can `require` and use it."
msgstr ""
"我们可以使用下划线的扩展，而不是由自己来实现的版本。安装后`underscore`` to "
"the ``node_modules`` directory, we can ``require`和使用它。 ???"

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:41
msgid "``` npm install underscore ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex/doc/how-to/require-3rd-party-libs.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"<script>\n"
"  var _ = require('underscore')\n"
"  var obj1 = {a: 1}\n"
"  var obj2 = {b: 2}\n"
"  var obj3 = {c: 3}\n"
"  var ret = _.extend(obj1, obj2, obj3) // ret => {a: 1, b: 2, c: 3}\n"
"</script>\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""